`tas2781_load_calibration()` builds a full `struct tasdevice_fw` object at [tas2781-fmwlib.c:2120]( /data/lifengjie/sec/data/codex_real_world_projects/linux_codex/sound/soc/codecs/tas2781-fmwlib.c:2120 ) and may allocate `programs` via [tas2781-fmwlib.c:1279]( /data/lifengjie/sec/data/codex_real_world_projects/linux_codex/sound/soc/codecs/tas2781-fmwlib.c:1279 ) and `configs` via [tas2781-fmwlib.c:1343]( /data/lifengjie/sec/data/codex_real_world_projects/linux_codex/sound/soc/codecs/tas2781-fmwlib.c:1343 ) before parsing calibrations. The only calibration cleanup is `tas2781_clear_calfirmware()` at [tas2781-fmwlib.c:2275]( /data/lifengjie/sec/data/codex_real_world_projects/linux_codex/sound/soc/codecs/tas2781-fmwlib.c:2275 ), and it frees only `calibrations` plus their `dev_blks`; it never frees `tas_fmw->programs` or `tas_fmw->configs`.
